{"lemma":"شَرِيعَةٌ","slug":"شَرِيعَةٌ","root":"ش.ر.ع","root_slug":"ش-ر-ع","root_link":"/words/roots/ش-ر-ع","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun_prop","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"شَرِيعَة","root":"شرع","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n22146"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B4%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%90%D9%8A%D8%B9%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"way, path","tags":["obsolete"],"examples":[{"text":"ثُمَّ جَعَلْنَاكَ عَلَى شَرِيعَةٍ مِّنَ ٱلْأَمْرِ فَٱتَّبِعْهَا وَلَا تَتَّبِعْ أَهْوَاءَ ٱلَّذِينَ لَا يَعْلَمُونَ","english":"\"And now have We set thee on a clear road of commandment; so follow it, and follow not the whims of those who know not.\" (Surah al-Jathiya, Āyah 18, translated by Marmaduke Pickthall)"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"law and legislation"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"shari'a, law","tags":["definite"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Compare Ge'ez ሥርዐት (śərʿät), Sabaean 𐩦𐩧𐩲 (s²rʿ)."},"ipa":["/ʃa.riː.ʕa/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n22146","headword_ar":"شَرِيعَةٌ","root":"$rE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma$oraEapN","text_ar":"مَشْرَعَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma$oruEapN","text_ar":"مَشْرُعَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma$oraEN","text_ar":"مَشْرَعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$araEN","text_ar":"شَرَعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, TA *) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA='K","text_ar":"مَا=ءٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iraAEu","text_ar":"شِرَاعُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A watering-place; a resort of drinkers"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"both men and beasts"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (S, O, K, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a place to which men come to drink therefrom and to draw water,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, * TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and into which they sometimes make their beasts to enter, to drink:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) but the term ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"m$rEp","text_ar":"مشرعة","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Az, Msb,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ryEp","text_ar":"شريعة"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) is not applied by the Arabs to any but ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a watering-place"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as is permanent, and apparent to the eye,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az, Msb, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like the water of rivers,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not water from which one draws with the well-rope:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az, Msb, TA:) the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ariyEapN","text_ar":"شَرِيعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$araAy^iEu","text_ar":"شَرَايِعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and that of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma$oraEapN","text_ar":"مَشْرَعَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma$oraEN","text_ar":"مَشْرَعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or of both] is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma$aAriEu","text_ar":"مَشَارِعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; which is also expl. as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gaps,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"breaches, in the banks of rivers or the like by which men or beasts come to water:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and [in like manner it is said that]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ariyEapN","text_ar":"شَرِيعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a place of descent to water:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a way to water."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd in v. 52.) ―         -b2-  And hence, (Lth, Kr, Msb, TA, and Bd ubi suprà,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~ariyEapu","text_ar":"الشَّرِيعَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Lth, Kr, S, Msb, K, &c.,) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~iroEapu","text_ar":"الشِّرْعَةُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, K, &c.,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~aroEu","text_ar":"الشَّرْعُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) signifies likewise"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~iynu","text_ar":"الدِّينُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb, and Bd ubi suprà;) because it is a way to the means of eternal life; (Bd ibid.;) or because of its manifestness; (Msb;) [i. e.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The religious law of God;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, Kr, S, O, K, * TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"consisting of such ordinances as those of fasting and prayer and pilgrimage"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, Kr, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the giving of the poorrate"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kr, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and marriage,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and other acts"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, Kr, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of piety,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of obedience to God,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of duty to Him and to men:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kr, TA:) pl. as above. (Msb.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ariyEapN","text_ar":"شَرِيعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A law, an ordinance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a statute:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a religion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"way of belief and practice in respect of religion:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr, TA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a way of belief or conduct that is manifest"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ibn-'Arafeh, Mgh, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and right"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ibn-'Arafeh, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in religion;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh;) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iroEapN","text_ar":"شِرْعَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","O","Msb","K","TA","Az","Lth","Kr","Fr"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}